<paragraph id="2B7B36ED9673FFF9FF4BFD7B7C2BC9FB" blockId="2.[151,1437,730,1330]" box="[151,1303,730,754]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">
<heading id="703381819673FFF9FF4BFD7B7C2BC9FB" box="[151,1303,730,754]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis id="19B0EAFF9673FFF9FF4BFD7B79FBC9FB" bold="true" box="[151,199,730,754]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">6, 7.</emphasis>
The situation both of 
<taxonomicName id="ECC44D6E9673FFF9FE67FD7B7A71C9FB" authority="pungitius (Linnaeus, 1758)" authorityName="pungitius (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[443,845,730,754]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gasterosteidae" genus="Pungitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gasterosteiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pungitius">
<emphasis id="19B0EAFF9673FFF9FE67FD7B7A71C9FB" box="[443,845,730,754]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">Pungitius pungitius (Linnaeus, 1758)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="ECC44D6E9673FFF9FC5FFD7B7C2BC9FB" authority="(Kessler, 1859)" baseAuthorityName="Kessler" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[899,1303,730,754]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gasterosteidae" genus="Pungitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gasterosteiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="platygaster">
<emphasis id="19B0EAFF9673FFF9FC5FFD7B7D55C9FB" box="[899,1129,730,754]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">Pungitius platygaster</emphasis>
(Kessler, 1859)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="63DE65669673FFF9FAC2FD7B7A14CE3B" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" type="description">
<paragraph id="2B7B36ED9673FFF9FAC2FD7B7D16C81F" blockId="2.[151,1437,730,1330]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">
are also explained with the following paragraph in the article of 
<bibRefCitation id="4F554B1C9673FFF9FD23FD5F7AE2C81F" author="Artuz, M. L. &amp; Fricke, R." box="[767,990,766,790]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" pagination="545 - 565" refId="ref3676" refString="Artuz, M. L. &amp; Fricke, R. (2019) The marine teleost fishes of the Sea of Marmara; an updated and annotated checklist. Zootaxa, 4565 (4), 545 - 565. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4565.4.9" type="journal article" year="2019">Artüz &amp; Fricke 2019</bibRefCitation>
P: 551
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2B7B36ED9673FFF9FF1AFC837BA1C830" blockId="2.[151,1437,730,1330]" box="[198,669,802,826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">Whereas both are occurs in brackish waters.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2B7B36ED9673FFF9FF1AFCE77BF2C8E7" blockId="2.[151,1437,730,1330]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis id="19B0EAFF9673FFF9FF1AFCE77BF2C8E7" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">
“Although some fish species predominantly live in fresh or brackish water, the unique hydrographic structure of Sea of Marmara, with a surface salinity of 18‰ near the Black Sea connection, allows the presence of these species. This includes the species Gasterosteus aculeatus, 
<taxonomicName id="ECC44D6E9673FFF9FD75FC2F7AB2C8AF" baseAuthorityName="Kessler" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[681,910,910,934]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gasterosteidae" genus="Pungitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gasterosteiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="platygaster">Pungitius platygaster</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="ECC44D6E9673FFF9FC19FC2F7DA6C8AC" authority="pungitius" authorityName="pungitius (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[965,1178,910,933]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gasterosteidae" genus="Pungitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gasterosteiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pungitius">Pungitius pungitius</taxonomicName>
. Gasterosteus aculeatus (as Gasterosteus trachurus) and 
<taxonomicName id="ECC44D6E9673FFF9FDFDFC137BCCC8C0" authority="pungitius" authorityName="pungitius (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[545,752,946,969]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gasterosteidae" genus="Pungitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gasterosteiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pungitius">Pungitius pungitius</taxonomicName>
(as Gasterosteus pungilius) were reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="4F554B1C9673FFF9FB04FC137CA4C8C3" author="Deveciyan, K." box="[1240,1432,946,970]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" refId="ref4118" refString="Deveciyan, K. (1915) Balik ve balikcilik. Duyun-i Osmaniye varidat-i mahsuse idare-yi merkeziyesi matbaasi, Istanbul, 60 pp. [in Ottomane]" type="book" year="1915">Deveciyan (1915)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="ECC44D6E9673FFF9FF29FC7678BBC8E7" baseAuthorityName="Kessler" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[245,391,982,1006]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gasterosteidae" genus="Pungitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gasterosteiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="platygaster">P. platygaster</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="4F554B1C9673FFF9FE71FC777B44C8E7" author="Slastenenko, E." box="[429,632,982,1006]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" refId="ref4648" refString="Slastenenko, E. (1955 - 1956) Karadeniz havzasi baliklari. Et ve Balik Kurumu Umum Mudurlugu Yayinlarindan, Istanbul, 762 pp. [in Turkish]" type="book" year="1955">
Slastenenko (
<date id="5F7A102D9673FFF9FDE0FC777B87C8E7" box="[572,699,982,1006]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" value="1955" valueMax="1956">1955-1956</date>
</bibRefCitation>
).”
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2B7B36ED9673FFF9FF1AFC5B781BCF77" blockId="2.[151,1437,730,1330]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">
Also in 
<bibRefCitation id="4F554B1C9673FFF9FEC0FC5B7B19CF1B" author="Ladiges, W. &amp; Vogt, D." box="[284,549,1018,1042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" refId="ref4331" refString="Ladiges, W. &amp; Vogt, D. (1965) Die Susswasserfische Europas bis zum Ural und Kaspischen Meer: Ein Taschenbuch fur Sport- und Berufsfischer, Biologen und Naturfreunde. Verlag Paul Parey, Hamburg and Berlin, 250 pp. [in German]" type="book" year="1965">Ladiges and Vogt (1965)</bibRefCitation>
is stated clearly on p: 176 
<emphasis id="19B0EAFF9673FFF9FC9DFC5A7A72CF1B" box="[833,846,1019,1042]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">–</emphasis>
177/ fish nr. 
<specimenCount id="3DC2FD649673FFF9FC04FC5B7D20CF1B" box="[984,1052,1018,1042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" type="generic">
187 
<taxonomicName id="ECC44D6E9673FFF9FBDBFC5A7D20CF1B" authorityName="pungitius (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1031,1052,1019,1042]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gasterosteidae" genus="Pungitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gasterosteiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pungitius">
<emphasis id="19B0EAFF9673FFF9FBDBFC5A7D20CF1B" box="[1031,1052,1019,1042]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">P.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</specimenCount>
pungitius as “ 
<emphasis id="19B0EAFF9673FFF9FB6AFC5B7820CF77" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">VORKOMMEN: Fast circumpolar, aber nicht so weit südwärts wie Gasterosteus. An den europäischen Küsten nur im nördlichen Eismeer, in Nord- und Ostsee und im Schwarzen Meer. An den atlantischen Küsten wahrscheinlich, im Mittelmeergebiet sicher fehlend.</emphasis>
“
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2B7B36ED9673FFF9FF4BFB2B78F7CFE3" blockId="2.[151,1437,730,1330]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">
- 
<emphasis id="19B0EAFF9673FFF9FF1AFB2B78F7CFE3" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">OCCURRENCE: Almost circumpolar, but not as far south as Gasterosteus. On the European coasts only in the north- ern polar sea, in the North and Baltic Sea and in the Black Sea. Probably on the Atlantic coasts, certainly missing in the Mediterranean area.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2B7B36ED9673FFF9FF1AFB577A14CE3B" blockId="2.[151,1437,730,1330]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">Without knowing the original characteristics of the water masses of the Sea of Marmara, the objection of the commenter based on his own article could not be understood.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
